Alexandria University ( Arabic : جامعة الإسكندرية ) is a university in Alexandria , Egypt . It was established in 1938 as a satellite of Fouad I University , becoming an independent entity in 1942 . It was known as Farouk University until it became the University of Alexandria in 1952 . Taha Hussein was the founding rector of Alexandria University . It is now the second largest university in Egypt and has many affiliations to various universities for ongoing research . In 1989 , four faculties , located in Alexandria and administered by Helwan University , were annexed to Alexandria University . These are the faculties of Agriculture , Fine Arts , Physical Education for boys and Physical Education for girls . List of Egyptian universities . This African university , college or other education institution article is a stub . 